diff:1384720425:1384110563:=97,98c97,98%0a%3c !WtF Locations%0a%3c %0a---%0a> !Savannah National Wildlife Refuge%0a> %0a100c100,109%0a%3c %0a---%0a> "Hey, If you listen closely you can hear the trees whispering. They talk about a lot of things. Mostly they talk about how they want to slide their roots through your flesh to fertilize the ground."'' - Turn-Key, Ithaeur of the Lords of Mourning Glory.%0a> %0a> In the territories of Savannah there is likely no place more important or revered to local werewolves than the Forest Heart, located in the center of the Savannah National Wildlife Refuge. This collection of forest and marshland is a powerful focus of spiritual energy, a place where leylines from across the land connect and cause the creation of loci. The Heart of the Forest is a powerful locus, offering rich stores of essence filled with a resonance of nature and decay.%0a> %0a> The laws of the wild are reflected in startling brutality on the other side of the barrier where spirits predate on one another, creating a treacherous domain full of entities that keep secrets buried deep underneath the water. This ideal territory also serves another purpose...%0a> %0a> It is a prison.%0a> %0a> It was during the end of the Brethren War that the Lords of Mourning Glory collected lesser packs to their beneath their rule, and with a few talented ritualists, were able to throw back the Pure Tribes and their strange totems. The most dangerous of these totems were bound and imprisoned when able, locked inside of dangerously treacherous fetishes that were then buried inside of living trees using Nature Gifts. These trees were then spiritually awakened and bound themselves to act as custodians for their prisoners, keeping these alien entities from the deep spirit wilds locked away.%0a> %0a103,142c112,144%0a%3c ''"What? Werewolves forming a city-state? I thought all shapeshifters just killed each other."'' - Deceased Intruder%0a%3c %0a%3c The grounds you enter are a clearing within the wilderness. It is a space surrounded by mighty trees that stretch up into the skyline like jagged teeth. The center of the clearing is dominated by a rock formation, altered by the Gifts of the People and inscribed with holy markings and sigils in reverence to all the things held most sacred by werewolves. %0a%3c %0a%3c There are many smaller boulders and rocks that surround the formation, providing seating at various heights. Those with greater status or influence in the city-state of werewolves are given seats closer to the a throne of bone and trophies located at the top. The pinnacle of the formation is as cold as winter's first breathe no matter the season. %0a%3c %0a%3c The throne is a pile of bones of various creatures, weapons, and trophies; cobbled and held together by ice and frost. The icey throne is blessed by powerful rituals, marking the area as a caern. This is where the Lord Alpha sits when he is listening to the requests and reports of the lesser packs.%0a%3c %0a%3c '''ACTIVE EFFECTS:''' Creating the Caern, Ward Against Humans, Ward Against Rage, Bind Human, Rite of Chosen Ground%0a%3c %0a%3c • Werewolves attempting violence against one%0a%3c another feel compelled not to do so, as if their limbs%0a%3c resist the very action. They can still attack, but doing%0a%3c so incurs a –4 penalty. (Defending from an attack,%0a%3c however, does not incur such a penalty.) The resistance%0a%3c (and thus, the penalty) can be removed if the%0a%3c werewolf wishing to bring about violence spends a%0a%3c Willpower point.%0a%3c %0a%3c • Upon approaching the cairn, every werewolf%0a%3c must choose a Social Skill bonus. This bonus%0a%3c provides a +1 die to any of the following Social%0a%3c Skills: Empathy, Expression, Persuasion, Socialize%0a%3c or Subterfuge. The werewolf must choose one of%0a%3c these Skills to boost while within the cairn’s radius%0a%3c of effect. This bonus is only good while within the%0a%3c cairn’s radius of effect. The Skill bonus is locked in%0a%3c until the next phase of the moon reaches its apex, at%0a%3c which point the werewolf can choose to change the%0a%3c bonus or keep it.%0a%3c %0a%3c • It is harder to enter Kuruth while within the%0a%3c affected cairn radius. Rolls to resist Death Rage are%0a%3c made at a +3 modifier.(Additional +1 for Ward Against Rage)%0a%3c %0a%3c • There is a resonance of Community that offers a +1 to all appropriate social rolls, such as Socialize, Persuasion, Empathy, etc.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!The Skinner Family Estate%0a%3c %0a%3c You see before you an old gothic-style manor, decorated by well kept lawns and gardens. The family crest, a wolf's head carrying a ring in its mouth, is reflected in much of the estate's architecture and design. There are three wings to the manor, offering an abundance of rooms for visiting members of the family or guests. The grounds of the estate lie close to the nearby swamps of Skidrow Island, casting a dark feeling upon the building and its inhabitants.%0a---%0a> The meeting ground of the Forsaken in Savannah is a copse of trees, grown in a circle, on a patch of raised ground. This piece of pristine wilderness is where the packs come together to interact and create ever shifting allegiances. There is a central bonfire that is lit at night to provide illumination, and werewolf Gifts have hollowed out the ground beneath the meeting spot, creating a council chamber where the packs' leaders and representatives can meet privately to discuss policy and future actions.%0a> %0a> This meeting chamber is a vast underground room, fortified by the living roots of the trees above. There exists in the central chamber a table, crafted from a still living tree, and a seat for every representative of each pack that claims membership in the Hegemony.%0a> %0a> It is rumored that sometimes spirits or stranger entities come calling on the werewolves for their own reasons, offering promises and favors in exchange for support in their own causes.%0a> %0a> !!Loci%0a> %0a> The Hegemony maintains several powerful loci, made possible only by the combined might of the packs aligned underneath the Alpha pack. This organization is rarely found among the Forsaken packs, but it has offered undeniable benefits:%0a> %0a> * Werewolves who are members of the Hegemony have an easier time accessing Essence to fuel their powers. They gain one Essence point per day, but may me rewarded with more for acting in service to the Hegemony.%0a> %0a> * Werewolves have access to the Shadow from any of the loci that dot the wilderness. The spirit wilds are "relatively" tame here and not as dangerous to traverse until you're one mile away from Hegemony territory.%0a> %0a> * Werewolves receive +1 to resist Death Rage and teamwork rolls while visiting the Tur. The use of Inspiration Gifts is periodically carried out to promote an atmosphere of cooperation and reduce the strain on a visiting werewolf's instincts.%0a> %0a> !!Wards & Guardians%0a> %0a> This is the center of Forsaken power in Savannah. The collective efforts of the packs underneath the Lords of Mourning Glory have yielded mighty protections. These protections are to maintain the security of the protectorate as much as keep its prisoners inside. There have been several incidents of attempted release of the totems locked inside their "cells" by the Pure Tribes.%0a> %0a> * Ward vs Humans / Bind Human: Any human (including Mages, Ghouls, Wolf-Blooded, and Sleepwalkers) attempting to enter into the wilderness feel a sensation of powerful foreboding that prevents entry. Wolf-blooded in service to the local packs are offered special tokens that allow them to ignore this effect. The token takes the form of a pine cone marked by the head ritualist's blood. This effect extends to 50 yards.%0a> %0a> * Rite of Moon's Love: Those Wolf-blooded who come to the werewolves to fulfill some matter of business or to perhaps curry favor form their relations receive this ritual. Thus they are offered some additional protection from Lunacy during their visit.%0a> %0a> * Wake the Spirit: There are spirit-awakened trees that serve as sentries into the territory. These spirits will alert the totems of every pack inside the area of intruders.%0a> %0a> * Rite of Chosen Ground: The spirit wilds have been reshaped to reflect the chosen qualities of the local packs. This is usually reflected in a resonance of nature or of the Hunt. A werewolf will receive +1 to actions involving survival while in the area.%0a> %0a> * U.S Fish & Wildlife Service: Wolf-blooded employed by Fish & Wildlife will routinely patrol the borders of the refuge, looking for both poachers and enemies of the People.%0a> %0a> !!The Lesser Packs%0a> %0a> There are five packs in total that owe fealty to the Lords of Mourning Glory. They act as enforcers for the protectorate, and usually will back any actions that are put forth by the Alpha pack. However they have their own internal grudges and motivations that may put them at odds with visitors or offer opportunities to get ahead in the bloody and violent politics of the Hegemony.%0a
