diff:1384110563:1383344884:=549c549%0a%3c -%3cCost: 1 Essence%0a---%0a> -%3cCost: None%0a552,553c552,553%0a%3c The Werewolf heightens their occult senses to the point where they can literally smell supernatural phenomena, allowing him to catch the distinct scents of all supernatural effects within his area. Beings, objects, locations, all fair game. The scents are nonspecific but generally give a sense of the nature of the magic and vague descriptor (person, place, or thing). Scent of Taint does not reveal the source of a magical effect, it merely makes it possible to seek out magic based on its supernatural nature alone. The Werewolf must still roll Wits + Composure to spot a supernatural entity, and hidden people/objects/locations are not automatically revealed. (Note: For the more rules obsessed, a magical occlusion effect, like invisibility or a ward, is itself considered to be occluded). (Note: The Gift user must defeat the initial activation roll of a power or effect that supernaturally conceals its user. They detect them with the Wits + Composure roll, factoring in appropriate penalties)%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The Werewolf heightens their occult senses to the point where they can literally smell supernatural phenomena, allowing him to catch the distinct scents of all supernatural effects within his area. Beings, objects, locations, all fair game. The scents are nonspecific but generally give a sense of the nature of the magic and vague descriptor (person, place, or thing). This effect is always active and is "pinged" when a supernatural power or phenomena occurs when in range.%0a> Scent of Taint does not reveal the source of a magical effect, it merely makes it possible to seek out magic based on its supernatural nature alone. The Werewolf must still roll Wits + Composure to spot a supernatural entity, and hidden people/objects/locations are not automatically revealed. (Note: For the more rules obsessed, a magical occlusion effect, like invisibility or a ward, is itself considered to be occluded). This gift allows a Clash roll versus Obfuscate, Wits + Investigation + Wisdom.%0a
