diff:1381199280:1379426573:=310,368c310,342%0a%3c (:table border="1" style="border-collapse:collapse" padding="5px":)%0a%3c (:headnr colspan=4 bgcolor=#74483f:)[[#CMG]]%25white%25Crescent Moon Gifts%25%25%0a%3c (:cellnr colspan=4:)''There is no increased cost for buying Between the Weave without Crash the Gates, or vice versa''.%0a%3c (:headnr:)Gift Name%0a%3c (:head:)Cost%0a%3c (:head:)Dice Pool%0a%3c (:head:)Action%0a%3c (:cellnr:)'''Gauntlet Cloak &#9679;&#9679;&#9679;'''%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cellnr colspan=4:)%0a%3c ->Success: The Ithaeur becomes shrouded in a cloak Gauntlet membrane, attempts to spot him or recognize him take a penalty equal to the number of successes on the activation roll, though the penalty can be no more than his highest Renown. The Werewolf is also treated as having a -2 concealment modifier vs ranged attacks, that stacks with natural concealment. This effect lasts the entire scene, may be activated reflexively at no cost whenever the Werewolf willingly crosses the Gauntlet.%0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:cellnr:)'''Crash the Gates &#9679;&#9679;&#9679;&#9679;'''%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)1 ess\\%0a%3c (+1 per packmate)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)Reflexive%0a%3c (:cellnr colspan=4:)%0a%3c ->Change: Same effects, but the placement is swapped with Between the Weave.%0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:cellnr:)'''Between the Weave &#9679;&#9679;&#9679;&#9679;&#9679;'''%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)1 Willpower%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)Manip+Occ+Wis%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)Extended\\%0a%3c (1 minute/roll)%0a%3c (:cellnr colspan=4:)%0a%3c ->Focusing on the small flaws inherent in the space between worlds the Werewolf selects one particular crack and briefly splits it open. This allows the Ithaeur to, very briefly, create a passable hole in the Shadow through which he and others can pass. This requires the Werewolf to sit and focus on spreading the gap, rolling in one minute intervals until he accrues enough successes (between 5 and 25, depending on Gauntlet density, at the Story Teller's discretion). Once open the portal functions exactly like a locus, save that it provides no essence and remains open for only a single scene. Canny spirits and other beings with proper perception might notice the hole being formed, but to do so requires a Wits + Composure roll at a -3 penalty.%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:headnr colspan=4 bgcolor=#74483f:)[[#DG]]%25white%25Death Gifts%25%25%0a%3c (:headnr:)Gift Name%0a%3c (:head:)Cost%0a%3c (:head:)Dice Pool%0a%3c (:head:)Action%0a%3c (:cellnr:)'''Ghost Knife &#9679;&#9679;'''%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cellnr colspan=4:)%0a%3c ->As written, but the duration is one day per dot of Wisdom the user possesses, minimum 1 day.%0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:cellnr:)'''Corpse Witness &#9679;&#9679;&#9679;'''%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cellnr colspan=4:)%0a%3c ->Change: The corpse can report on events that transpired beyond the physical. It can gift summaries of conversations, descriptions of smells or explain that it had "a bumpy ride". When invoked the Werewolf can ask the corpse a number of questions equal to the rolled successes on the Gift activation, though without an exceptional success the corpse's intelligence is piddling. This recall is not limited to one day and night, but gets worse the further back the corpse must "remember".%0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:cellnr:)'''Vengeance of the Slaine &#9679;&#9679;&#9679;&#9679;&#9679;'''%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cell align=center:)%0a%3c (:cellnr colspan=4:)%0a%3c ->Same, but add: By spending an additional point of willpower each success instead returns the body to subject to life for one day per success.%0a%3c -----%0a%3c -----%0a%3c (:tableend:)%0a---%0a> !!!Crescent Moon Gifts%0a> (:toggle hide cmg:)%0a> >>id